<div id="review_1851968018" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1851968018" />
    <a title="Laysee" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/4863523-laysee"><img alt="Laysee" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1459741824p2/4863523.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1851968018?book_show_action=true">Dec 26, 2016</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Laysee" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Laysee" href="/user/show/4863523-laysee">Laysee</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1851968018" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10138694300850527013"><br/>Dylan Thomas is a Welsh poet known for his poem, &quot;Do not go gently into that good night.&quot; I am thrilled to learn he has written a prose poem about Christmas. This tiny book described his experience of Christmas &quot;years and years ago, when (he) was a boy&quot; in Wales. It contained some truly lush and beautiful lines about snow and captured the nostalgia associated with Christmas at a time when life was relatively simpler.<br/><br/>If you love poetry, you will most certainly find this an enchanting treat. In Th</span>
  <span id="freeText10138694300850527013" style="display:none"><br />Dylan Thomas is a Welsh poet known for his poem, "Do not go gently into that good night." I am thrilled to learn he has written a prose poem about Christmas. This tiny book described his experience of Christmas "years and years ago, when (he) was a boy" in Wales. It contained some truly lush and beautiful lines about snow and captured the nostalgia associated with Christmas at a time when life was relatively simpler.<br /><br />If you love poetry, you will most certainly find this an enchanting treat. In Thomas' recollections were fond memories of one Christmas day: "the muffling silence of the eternal snows", snowballing the cats in his neighborhood, turkey and blazing pudding for dinner, singing carols "in the snow-felted darkness", playing in the snow in his bright new boots, and Auntie Hannah who "laced her tea with rum, because it was only once a year."<br /><br />This gem deserves five sparkling snow-lit stars. </span>
  <a data-text-id="10138694300850527013" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


